node.title: Victoria records 1,007 new COVID-19 cases and 12 deaths
node.alt: Shoppers both seated and walking in a Melbourne arcade with a Christmas tree in the background.
node.description: There are now 13,814 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 445 people have died during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,007\u00a0new COVID-19 cases and 12 deaths.", "There are now 13,814 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 445\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak.", "There are 337\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 63\u00a0are in intensive care, and 34\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 65\u00a0people were in intensive care but their infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 72,270\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 6,315\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has now fully vaccinated 88\u00a0per cent of its population aged 12 and over.", "More to come.", "", "
WA's COVID-19 reopening roadmap
